* Implementation of the {@code IBrailleDisplayController} AIDL interface provided to * system_server, which system_server uses to pass messages back to this * {@code BrailleDisplayController}. * *

Messages from system_server are routed to the {@link BrailleDisplayCallback} callbacks * implemented by the accessibility service. * *

Note: Per API Guidelines 7.5 the Binder identity must be cleared before invoking the * callback executor so that Binder identity checks in the callbacks are performed using the * app's identity.

methods.name: public void onConnected(IBrailleDisplayConnection connection, byte[] hidDescriptor)
methods.comment: * Called when the system successfully connects to a Braille display.

methods.name: public void onConnectionFailed(@BrailleDisplayCallback.ErrorCode int errorCode)
methods.comment: * Called when the system is unable to connect to a Braille display.

methods.name: public void onInput(byte[] input)
methods.comment: * Called when input is received from the currently connected Braille display.

methods.name: public void onDisconnected()
methods.comment: * Called when the currently connected Braille display is disconnected.
